com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.beans

Class BeanExpressionCondition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.AbstractDataCondition<ISharedBeanDescriptor,ISharedBean,IBeanQuery,IBeanQueryResult>
      • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.beans.BeanExpressionCondition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBeanCondition, IDataCondition<ISharedBeanDescriptor,ISharedBean,IBeanQuery,IBeanQueryResult>

    public class BeanExpressionCondition
extends AbstractDataCondition<ISharedBeanDescriptor,ISharedBean,IBeanQuery,IBeanQueryResult>
implements IBeanCondition
    Enables JEXL-format expressions over beans. The following instance data are available to the expression.
    • Local - a map of bean names to beans available in the local platform evaluating the condition (see below).
    • Peer - a map of bean names to beans available on one of the remote platforms within the set of peer applications.
    • Average - provides access to the averages of bean values across beans from a set of peers
    • Sum - provides access to the sum of bean values across beans from a set of peers
    • Min - provides access to the min of bean values across beans from a set of peers
    • Max - provides access to the max of bean values across beans from a set of peers
    • Count - provides access to the count of bean values across beans from a set of peers
    The Peer and aggregators (Average, etc) instances may not be used in the same expression. All of these instances provide a get method with additional signatures for the aggregators, as follows:
    • get(String beanName) - gets the bean with the given name.
    • get(String beanName, String memberName) - available only on the aggregators to allow aggregations on fields or zero-arg methods of the object with the given name. The field or method must return a primitive value or an instance of java.lang.Number.

    Examples

    • Local.get("memory") > Peer.get("memory") - Assumes 'memory' is an instance of Number stored in the platform.
    • Local.get("stats").uptime() < Peer.get("stats").uptime() - 'stats' is an application object stored with the platform that has an uptime() method that returns a Number or primitive value.
    • Local.get("memory") < Average.get("memory") - similar to the first, but compares the local value of 'memory' against the average of the 'memory' of all peer results.
    • Local.get("stats").uptime() < Average.get("stats", "uptime()") - similar to the 2nd, but averages the uptimes of all peers.

    dawood

      • isAggregate

        public boolean isAggregate()
        Description copied from interface: IDataCondition
        Return true if this condition is a condition across results from multiple peers. Otherwise it is a pair-wise condition between the local data and the data from a single remote peer. If the condition is used with a subscription to multiple peers and is not aggregate, then the condition will be fired for each separate peer as their data arrives.
